article.description: Dwight Murray Jr. came off the bench to score 15 points to carry Incarnate Word to an 86-60 win over Division III-member Texas Lutheran on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Murray Jr. carries Incarnate Word over Texas Lutheran 86-60
article.linkText: Murray Jr. carries Incarnate Word over Texas Lutheran 86-60
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Dwight Murray Jr. came off the bench to score 15 points to carry Incarnate Word to an 86-60 win over Division III-member Texas Lutheran on Tuesday night. Vincent Miszkiewicz had 12 points for Incarnate Word (1-2). Drew Lutz and Bryce Davis added 10 points apiece. Sebastian Andrade had 11 points and Jorden Kite added 10 for the Bulldogs. Incarnate Word plays Southern Illinois-Edwardsville at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
